l and literary arts at differing levels of sophistication, they were all guided by a sense that there exist deep ontological and epistemological bonds between computational and verbal thinking and production. Their shared view that a network or continuity exists between the arts yielded extraordinary results. Through measuring their words, literally and figuratively, they are models of what the very best interdisciplinary work can offer us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMathematical literaturezItalyxHistoryy15th century. 0aMathematical literaturezItalyxHistoryy16th century. 0aMathematicszItalyxHistoryy15th century. 0aMathematicszItalyxHistoryy16th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aGiambattista Della Porta.  aItalian history.  aLeon Battista Alberti.  aLuca Pacioli.  aNiccolò Tartaglia.  aRenaissance art history.  acomputation.  acryptography.  acubic equations.  ahistory of mathematics.  aliterature.  amath.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751330640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487513306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487513306.jpg  a978-3-11-066594-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles